er all manner and form of complaint to the Tribunal, regardless of its merits. This is why it enjoys the powers of investigation.  At the same time, in order to ensure that complainants\'92 interests are adequately addressed, the Commission is obliged to inve
stigate a complaint lodged by a third party.    }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\ql\rtlch\af0\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f0\fs24\lang2057\loch\f0\fs24\lang2057 
